| Scenario | mbuzz | Dreamdata |
|----------|-------|-----------|
| Testing attribution | Free (both) | Free (both) |
| Small B2B team | $29-99/mo | $750/mo |
| Growing B2B team | $99-299/mo | $750-2,250/mo |
| Enterprise B2B | $299/mo | Custom pricing |

Both have free tiers for evaluation — a major advantage over competitors like HockeyStack ($1,399+ minimum).

See [Dreamdata Pricing](/articles/dreamdata-pricing) for a complete breakdown of tiers, hidden costs, and alternatives.

## Choose Dreamdata If...

- Journey visualization is your #1 priority
- Deep LinkedIn audience activation matters
- You want deeper out-of-box CRM integrations
- You can invest 4-8 weeks in setup
- You need established brand recognition for procurement
- Content performance analytics are important

## Choose mbuzz If...

- Model transparency and flexibility are priorities (8 models + custom rules)
- You want to deploy in days, not weeks
- Budget matters ($29-299 vs $750/mo)
- Server-side tracking accuracy is important
- You need custom attribution logic on all tiers
- Data ownership and no lock-in matter

## The Verdict

**Dreamdata** suits mid-market B2B teams ($10-50M) who value journey visualization, LinkedIn audience activation, and have 4-8 weeks for implementation and $750+/mo budget. Journey visualization is genuinely best-in-class — if that's your primary need, Dreamdata is hard to beat.

**mbuzz** suits technical B2B teams who want model flexibility, fast setup, and lower cost. Server-side tracking and custom attribution rules deployed in days instead of weeks. If model transparency matters more than visual journeys, mbuzz delivers that.

The overlap question: both have free tiers. Start with both and see which delivers more value for your specific B2B context.

